1
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:12,700
<i> If Danilo loves you,</i>

2
00:00:12,833 --> 00:00:16,200
<i>he won't give in to Jade
no matter what she does!</i>

3
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:19,700
<i>Maybe Emma hates me so much
that she wants to get even.</i>

4
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:22,267
<i>And she found an ally in Logan.</i>

5
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:23,967
<i>I have no reason
not to forget her.</i>

6
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:26,233
<i>I won't let her get
near my daughter.</i>

7
00:00:26,367 --> 00:00:29,300
<i>I will help Emma
get Mookie back.</i>

8
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:34,167
<i>But I'll make sure she doesn't
talk to Danilo anymore.</i>

9
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:35,433
<i> How's Miss Emma?</i>

10
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:37,633
<i>I don't want to talk
about her anymore.</i>

11
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:38,533
<i> Where are you going?</i>

12
00:00:38,667 --> 00:00:39,267
<i> What are you doing?</i>

13
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:41,300
<i> Don't make a scene here!</i>

14
00:00:41,433 --> 00:00:42,133
<i> Bastard!</i>

15
00:00:43,100 --> 00:00:44,567
<i>- Mookie.
- Mom?</i>

16
00:00:44,700 --> 00:00:46,533
<i>- Mookie, Dear.
- What are you doing here?</i>

17
00:00:46,667 --> 00:00:48,000
<i> Mr. Guard, please help me.</i>

18
00:00:48,133 --> 00:00:49,933
<i> This woman is harassing me.</i>

19
00:00:50,067 --> 00:00:52,300
<i> Dear, let me explain.</i>

20
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:53,167
<i> Dear.</i>

21
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:54,267
<i>- This way, Ma'am.
- Mookie!</i>

22
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:34,067
Anne Gomez.

23
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,567
This is the wedding planner
I found

24
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:38,100
who agreed to plan your wedding
in three months.

25
00:01:38,233 --> 00:01:39,200
She was challenged.

26
00:01:44,133 --> 00:01:45,700
Jade?

27
00:01:45,833 --> 00:01:46,567
Are you okay?

28
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:53,500
Jade?

29
00:01:53,633 --> 00:01:54,300
I'm sorry.

30
00:01:54,433 --> 00:01:56,500
It's just that...

31
00:01:56,633 --> 00:02:00,133
Emma still doesn't stop.

32
00:02:00,267 --> 00:02:02,900
She's still bothering us.

33
00:02:03,033 --> 00:02:04,200
And Danilo...

34
00:02:06,200 --> 00:02:09,667
<i> This isn't true.</i>

35
00:02:09,800 --> 00:02:15,433
<i>I wonder why we couldn't find
Emma when we looked for her.</i>

36
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,500
<i>You know what? This isn't true!</i>

37
00:02:27,267 --> 00:02:30,833
I need to find a way
to stop all these.

38
00:02:30,967 --> 00:02:33,167
To stop Emma.

39
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:37,000
Call that Anne Gomez and tell
her I will double the pay

40
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:39,833
to arrange the wedding
in one month.

41
00:02:39,967 --> 00:02:41,633
What? One month?

42
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:42,733
That's impossible.

43
00:02:44,167 --> 00:02:45,833
Just please do it, Astrid.

44
00:02:54,533 --> 00:02:55,167
This way, Ma'am.

45
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,500
- Mookie!
- Go on, please.

46
00:03:15,533 --> 00:03:16,400
What happened?

47
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:20,000
Mookie's mad at me.

48
00:03:20,133 --> 00:03:21,833
She doesn't want to talk to me.

49
00:03:23,600 --> 00:03:26,467
What you did is
so harsh, Mooks.

50
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,267
You disrespected Miss Emma.

51
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:30,367
She's still your mother.

52
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:31,767
Zayn!

53
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:35,333
She disrespected
Dad and me first.

54
00:03:35,467 --> 00:03:37,767
She only wanted
to talk to you.

55
00:03:37,900 --> 00:03:40,267
I wish you had
given her a chance.

56
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,233
There's no need for that.

57
00:03:42,367 --> 00:03:43,733
Aunt Jade told me everything.

58
00:03:43,867 --> 00:03:46,967
She left us for another man.

59
00:03:47,100 --> 00:03:52,133
All your assumptions only came
from what Aunt Jade told you.

60
00:03:52,267 --> 00:03:54,767
Not directly from Miss Emma.

61
00:03:54,933 --> 00:03:57,433
You still need to listen
to your mother

62
00:03:57,567 --> 00:04:00,833
before deciding whether
you'll believe her.

63
00:04:00,967 --> 00:04:04,900
Or at least check the
proof of what she says.

64
00:04:08,533 --> 00:04:13,167
The Mookie I know
listens to both sides.

65
00:04:13,300 --> 00:04:15,500
And is not quick to judge.

66
00:04:15,633 --> 00:04:17,100
Just like before.

67
00:04:17,233 --> 00:04:19,767
Even though your Mommy
Olive was hurting you,

68
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:21,633
you gave her a chance
to explain.

69
00:04:21,767 --> 00:04:24,367
And to answer your questions.

70
00:04:24,500 --> 00:04:28,467
I hope you do the same
to Miss Emma, Mooks.

71
00:04:28,633 --> 00:04:30,600
Look.

72
00:04:30,733 --> 00:04:33,767
I'm sorry if you feel
like I interfere.

73
00:04:33,900 --> 00:04:37,333
But all I want you to do
is give Miss Emma a chance.

74
00:04:37,467 --> 00:04:41,700
Mooks, I can see
how much she loves you.

75
00:04:41,833 --> 00:04:44,533
She even fought for you.

76
00:04:44,667 --> 00:04:48,833
I can't believe she'll
leave you just like that.

77
00:05:53,767 --> 00:05:54,533
Wait.

78
00:05:54,667 --> 00:05:55,433
Where are you going?

79
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,200
You're right, Zayn.

80
00:06:00,100 --> 00:06:03,133
I need to hear
Mom's explanation.

81
00:06:13,500 --> 00:06:15,900
Jade poisoned my
daughter's mind.

82
00:06:16,033 --> 00:06:17,233
She doesn't want me anymore.

83
00:06:19,033 --> 00:06:20,733
But I won't let that happen.

84
00:06:20,867 --> 00:06:23,600
I'll do everything to
get my daughter back.

85
00:06:25,433 --> 00:06:26,567
That's right.

86
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:28,733
Once I get my daughter,
we'll leave the country.

87
00:06:28,867 --> 00:06:31,000
Let's go somewhere far.

88
00:06:31,133 --> 00:06:33,233
Far from here.

89
00:06:33,367 --> 00:06:35,367
I don't care about
what others will say.

90
00:06:35,500 --> 00:06:36,633
What's important is...

91
00:06:36,767 --> 00:06:38,167
What's important?

92
00:06:42,267 --> 00:06:43,367
Mookie.

93
00:06:43,500 --> 00:06:45,400
What matters is
you're with that man.

94
00:06:45,533 --> 00:06:46,600
Is that it?

95
00:06:46,733 --> 00:06:48,133
No.

96
00:06:48,267 --> 00:06:49,000
Mookie, that's not it.

97
00:06:49,133 --> 00:06:50,400
It's okay.

98
00:06:50,533 --> 00:06:51,967
Fine.

99
00:06:52,100 --> 00:06:55,433
I've known for a long time that
we don't matter to you anymore.

100
00:06:55,567 --> 00:06:59,000
And I've long accepted
that you're gone.

101
00:06:59,133 --> 00:07:00,300
Mookie.

102
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:04,200
- Mookie.
- Mookie, that's enough.

103
00:07:04,333 --> 00:07:06,600
No, Zayn.

104
00:07:07,667 --> 00:07:10,900
That's why I wonder
why you came back.

105
00:07:11,033 --> 00:07:13,900
Why did you have
to show up to me?

106
00:07:14,033 --> 00:07:15,100
Mookie, listen to me first...

107
00:07:15,267 --> 00:07:18,133
Maybe you're thinking that
I'm still the weak Mookie.

108
00:07:20,233 --> 00:07:22,533
Well, I'm no longer the
Mookie that you know.

109
00:07:22,667 --> 00:07:24,667
I can manage on my own.

110
00:07:24,800 --> 00:07:25,833
Mookie, Dear.

111
00:07:25,967 --> 00:07:27,067
- Please hear me out.
- What are you doing?

112
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:30,600
Don't touch me!

113
00:07:30,733 --> 00:07:32,067
You know what?

114
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:35,133
I wanted to give you
a chance to explain yourself.

115
00:07:36,933 --> 00:07:38,633
And this is what I heard?

116
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,467
You're so bad.

117
00:07:43,600 --> 00:07:44,500
Do you know that?

118
00:07:44,633 --> 00:07:46,067
You're so bad.

119
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:50,467
Dear, listen to me first.

120
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,733
Hear me out.

121
00:07:51,867 --> 00:07:52,667
No!

122
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:56,367
Just go.

123
00:07:57,267 --> 00:07:59,067
Get lost!

124
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:02,067
Leave us alone!

125
00:08:02,200 --> 00:08:03,500
Mookie.

126
00:08:03,633 --> 00:08:05,400
Fine!

127
00:08:05,533 --> 00:08:07,467
I'll just go.

128
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:08,867
Mookie, Dear.

129
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,567
Hey!

130
00:08:10,700 --> 00:08:12,167
Mookie, hear me out first.

131
00:08:14,000 --> 00:08:16,067
What else should
I need to hear?

132
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:19,933
Okay.

133
00:08:20,067 --> 00:08:21,433
Do you want to know the truth?

134
00:08:23,667 --> 00:08:25,100
Yes, I love Aunt Jade.

135
00:08:27,500 --> 00:08:29,067
But even though I love her,

136
00:08:31,400 --> 00:08:33,233
I don't want her and Dad
to get married.

137
00:08:34,933 --> 00:08:36,833
Do you know why?

138
00:08:36,967 --> 00:08:38,333
You're my mother.

139
00:08:40,767 --> 00:08:42,100
You and Dad are my family.

140
00:08:42,233 --> 00:08:44,700
You are my parents.

141
00:08:44,833 --> 00:08:46,967
I want you to get
back together.

142
00:08:48,733 --> 00:08:51,067
So even if it hurts,

143
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:53,400
even though I'm upset
with you...

144
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,467
Here I am...

145
00:09:00,867 --> 00:09:03,633
Still hoping you'll come back.

146
00:09:03,767 --> 00:09:06,367
That you'll come
back to me and Dad.

147
00:09:06,500 --> 00:09:11,733
I heard a lot of bad things
about you from Aunt Jade.

148
00:09:11,867 --> 00:09:17,733
But Zayn made me realize that
you might have an explanation.

149
00:09:19,533 --> 00:09:20,833
But no.

150
00:09:20,967 --> 00:09:24,433
All my questions
have been answered.

151
00:09:24,567 --> 00:09:27,367
You just proved Aunt Jade right.

152
00:09:27,500 --> 00:09:29,633
So, fine.

153
00:09:29,800 --> 00:09:33,333
Fine! Be with your lover!

154
00:09:34,567 --> 00:09:36,000
Mookie, Mookie.

155
00:09:36,133 --> 00:09:38,267
Mookie, hear me out first.

156
00:09:38,400 --> 00:09:39,667
It's not what you think.

157
00:09:39,800 --> 00:09:42,100
Logan and I aren't
in a relationship.

158
00:09:42,233 --> 00:09:43,433
Jade is just making up stories
about me.

159
00:09:43,567 --> 00:09:44,600
What am I?

160
00:09:47,233 --> 00:09:49,400
Am I a kid?

161
00:09:49,533 --> 00:09:57,233
Am I a gullible kid who will
believe everything you say?

162
00:09:57,367 --> 00:09:59,767
I want you to leave.

163
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:01,700
I want you to stop
showing up to us.

164
00:10:01,867 --> 00:10:02,967
That's what I want.

165
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:04,033
- Mookie.
- Zayn, let's go.

166
00:10:04,167 --> 00:10:05,167
Mookie, wait!

167
00:10:05,300 --> 00:10:06,233
I'm sorry.

168
00:10:06,367 --> 00:10:07,767
- Mookie, please talk to me.
- Come on, Zayn!

169
00:10:07,900 --> 00:10:08,500
Mookie!

170
00:10:08,633 --> 00:10:09,700
There's nothing you can do.

171
00:10:09,833 --> 00:10:11,500
Stop.

172
00:10:11,633 --> 00:10:13,533
Mookie!

173
00:10:13,667 --> 00:10:15,433
Mookie, please!

174
00:10:15,567 --> 00:10:17,800
You might get an accident.

175
00:10:17,933 --> 00:10:18,900
Mookie!

176
00:10:20,933 --> 00:10:22,333
What are you doing? Let me go!

177
00:10:22,467 --> 00:10:24,267
- That's enough!
- My daughter and I

178
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:26,433
could've talked if you hadn't
stopped me!

179
00:10:26,567 --> 00:10:27,800
You saw it.

180
00:10:27,933 --> 00:10:29,733
Your daughter doesn't
respect you anymore.

181
00:10:29,867 --> 00:10:31,300
And you're still
going to chase her?

182
00:10:31,433 --> 00:10:33,133
It's none of your business!

183
00:10:33,267 --> 00:10:36,067
It is. Because I love you.

184
00:10:36,233 --> 00:10:38,333
What did you say?

185
00:10:38,467 --> 00:10:40,200
Isn't it obvious?

186
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:42,467
Emma, I love you!

187
00:10:42,600 --> 00:10:44,067
If your daughter doesn't
want you,

188
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:46,833
choose me instead!

189
00:10:46,967 --> 00:10:48,233
Emma, I won't hurt you.

190
00:10:49,567 --> 00:10:50,867
So, please.

191
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:52,767
Just choose me.

192
00:10:52,900 --> 00:10:55,900
Because I will love you,
unlike what your daughter did.

193
00:11:08,467 --> 00:11:09,567
Did you see that, Love?

194
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:11,000
Over there?

195
00:11:11,133 --> 00:11:16,100
So, eventually, we can still
expand over there.

196
00:11:16,233 --> 00:11:18,633
I hate her!

197
00:11:18,767 --> 00:11:20,167
- Mookie!
- Why?

198
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:21,033
Why?

199
00:11:21,167 --> 00:11:23,533
- Baby girl, what's wrong?
- Why?

200
00:11:23,667 --> 00:11:27,667
Mom will leave again.

201
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:30,633
She chose that man over me!

202
00:11:33,967 --> 00:11:36,133
Oh, Mookie, baby girl.

203
00:11:36,267 --> 00:11:37,733
That's unbelievable.

204
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:42,367
You know what?

205
00:11:42,533 --> 00:11:45,100
Mommy Olive was better
than Mom

206
00:11:45,233 --> 00:11:48,233
even though she did many bad
things to me.

207
00:11:49,967 --> 00:11:52,500
Because she never left
me for another man.

208
00:11:52,633 --> 00:11:54,267
That's right, baby girl.

209
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:57,367
Olive can never do that.

210
00:11:57,500 --> 00:12:02,400
What your Mommy Emma
did is unforgivable.

211
00:12:02,533 --> 00:12:06,300
She ruined your family!

212
00:12:06,433 --> 00:12:07,400
Unbelievable!

213
00:12:10,800 --> 00:12:13,633
But don't worry.

214
00:12:13,767 --> 00:12:16,367
We can still fix this.

215
00:12:16,533 --> 00:12:20,933
From now on,
we're going to be a family.

216
00:12:23,367 --> 00:12:29,267
We will build a happy world
where Emma doesn't exist,

217
00:12:29,400 --> 00:12:30,900
just the three of us.

218
00:12:32,933 --> 00:12:35,667
In fact, Love...

219
00:12:37,033 --> 00:12:40,700
I found a wedding planner.

220
00:12:41,967 --> 00:12:46,933
I want us to get
married soon.

221
00:12:47,067 --> 00:12:51,200
So that I can fix
Mookie's adoption papers.

222
00:12:51,367 --> 00:12:55,467
But, of course, that is
if it's okay with both of you.

223
00:12:57,500 --> 00:13:00,900
You're right, Jade.

224
00:13:01,033 --> 00:13:02,867
We need to get married soon.

225
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:06,000
- Really?
- So Emma can't bother us.

226
00:13:06,133 --> 00:13:07,133
You're right.

227
00:13:07,267 --> 00:13:09,533
That's right, Auntie.

228
00:13:09,667 --> 00:13:12,500
Let's remove Mom
from our lives.

229
00:13:15,067 --> 00:13:20,433
Baby girl, from now on,
it's no longer Auntie.

230
00:13:21,833 --> 00:13:25,600
You will now call me Mommy.

231
00:13:25,733 --> 00:13:28,567
Mommy Jade.

232
00:13:28,700 --> 00:13:30,867
And another thing...

233
00:13:35,300 --> 00:13:40,200
our rebel stage should end.

234
00:13:40,333 --> 00:13:46,567
I want you to go back
to the old Mookie I know.

235
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:54,367
The sweet, jolly, happy Mookie
that I have gotten to know.

236
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:56,233
Okay?

237
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,233
There!

238
00:13:57,367 --> 00:14:00,367
My baby girl is so pretty.

239
00:14:14,133 --> 00:14:15,867
You're driving me nuts.

240
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:17,800
I only dropped by here to ask

241
00:14:17,933 --> 00:14:20,800
if you know a job
I can apply for.

242
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:23,667
But what I got is gossip.

243
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:24,667
Of course.

244
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:27,067
- You talked to us.
- What can you expect?

245
00:14:27,200 --> 00:14:28,833
Emma!

246
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:30,433
- Emma!
- Emma!

247
00:14:33,167 --> 00:14:34,400
- Come here!
- Let's help her!

248
00:14:34,533 --> 00:14:36,467
- Give it to me!
- Get her bag.

249
00:14:36,600 --> 00:14:37,567
Come here. Come here.

250
00:14:37,700 --> 00:14:38,833
Sit down.

251
00:14:38,967 --> 00:14:41,467
We were just talking
about you earlier.

252
00:14:41,600 --> 00:14:44,467
Yeah. You were gone for so long!

253
00:14:44,600 --> 00:14:46,167
One at a time.

254
00:14:46,300 --> 00:14:47,700
I will answer all
your questions.

255
00:14:47,833 --> 00:14:48,667
I will tell you everything.

256
00:14:48,800 --> 00:14:49,467
Okay, okay.

257
00:14:49,600 --> 00:14:51,167
Let's sit down.

258
00:14:51,300 --> 00:14:52,233
Okay, go on.

259
00:14:58,700 --> 00:15:02,533
Marco, is the address
you gave me correct?

260
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:04,167
I think I'm already lost.

261
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:05,200
<i> Yes, boss.</i>

262
00:15:05,333 --> 00:15:07,233
<i>Emma and her family lived
at Wiro's house</i>

263
00:15:07,367 --> 00:15:08,933
<i> before moving to Jade's.</i>

264
00:15:09,067 --> 00:15:10,933
<i>That's the only place
she can go to.</i>

265
00:15:11,067 --> 00:15:12,167
Excuse me.

266
00:15:12,300 --> 00:15:14,100
Does someone named
Wiro live here?

267
00:15:14,233 --> 00:15:15,233
Maybe you know him.

268
00:15:15,367 --> 00:15:17,767
I'm just new here, boss.

269
00:15:17,900 --> 00:15:20,100
Ask those who are playing.

270
00:15:20,233 --> 00:15:21,200
Okay, thank you.

271
00:15:26,400 --> 00:15:27,767
Excuse me.

272
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:30,400
Do you know any
Wiro who lives here?

273
00:15:30,533 --> 00:15:33,900
Go straight and turn right
to the first corner.

274
00:15:34,033 --> 00:15:35,467
Then, ask around.

275
00:15:35,633 --> 00:15:38,300
On that corner?

276
00:15:38,433 --> 00:15:38,967
Yes, Sir.

277
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:40,100
Okay.

278
00:15:40,233 --> 00:15:41,033
Thank you.

279
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,567
And that's what happened.

280
00:15:45,700 --> 00:15:47,567
That's why I didn't
show up sooner.

281
00:15:47,700 --> 00:15:49,700
I didn't tell Mom, too.

282
00:15:49,833 --> 00:15:52,100
I don't want her to get
in trouble because of me.

283
00:15:52,233 --> 00:15:53,333
Silly girl.

284
00:15:53,467 --> 00:15:56,600
Ligaya also learned about
Danilo and Jade's affair.

285
00:15:56,733 --> 00:15:58,433
She was so mad.

286
00:16:00,267 --> 00:16:01,733
Where is she?

287
00:16:01,867 --> 00:16:03,233
I can't contact her.

288
00:16:03,367 --> 00:16:05,233
We can't reach her, too.

289
00:16:05,367 --> 00:16:07,267
But when I called Danilo,

290
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:10,367
he told me that Ligaya
returned to Cebu

291
00:16:10,533 --> 00:16:12,367
because she was so angry.

292
00:16:12,500 --> 00:16:17,700
And she was upset with you
because you disappeared.

293
00:16:19,767 --> 00:16:20,867
It's okay.

294
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:26,467
She might get hypertensive
if she hears the latest events.

295
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:28,033
Wait, let's change the topic.

296
00:16:28,167 --> 00:16:30,867
Why did you leave your boss?

297
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,267
Didn't he help you
a lot already?

298
00:16:34,400 --> 00:16:37,600
He even hired you as
a manager of his bar.

299
00:16:37,733 --> 00:16:41,800
Is there a chance that you can
help me get a job there?

300
00:16:41,967 --> 00:16:42,833
Oh, come on, Flor.

301
00:16:42,967 --> 00:16:45,033
Do you really have
to make it about you?

302
00:16:45,167 --> 00:16:47,000
But I'm curious, too, Emma.

303
00:16:47,133 --> 00:16:49,667
What happened to you and Logan?

304
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:53,900
Based on what you told us,
he seemed a good person.

305
00:16:54,033 --> 00:16:55,367
Oh, there's a handsome guy.

306
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:56,133
Where?

307
00:16:58,933 --> 00:17:00,300
Are you referring to me?

308
00:17:03,133 --> 00:17:05,000
Logan.

309
00:17:05,133 --> 00:17:06,667
Wow!

310
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:09,000
You're outfit looks
uncomfortable.

311
00:17:09,133 --> 00:17:10,367
He looks like a magician.

312
00:17:12,367 --> 00:17:14,667
May I talk with Emma?

313
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:15,700
Go on.

314
00:17:15,867 --> 00:17:16,733
We'll be right here.

315
00:17:16,867 --> 00:17:17,867
We're not going to listen.

316
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,800
Yes.

317
00:17:19,933 --> 00:17:26,567
Emma, I know and understand
that you're mad at me.

318
00:17:26,700 --> 00:17:28,333
Sorry.

319
00:17:28,467 --> 00:17:30,733
I didn't mean it.

320
00:17:30,867 --> 00:17:33,100
Can you please come home?

321
00:17:33,233 --> 00:17:35,367
Emma, you're safer there.

322
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:39,067
It's okay if you don't
want to see or be with me.

323
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:40,733
I'll go.

324
00:17:40,867 --> 00:17:42,267
I'll stay in the other condo.

325
00:17:44,633 --> 00:17:46,500
Don't say no.

326
00:17:46,633 --> 00:17:49,333
He has a lot of gold.

327
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:51,300
And you can't stay at my house.

328
00:17:51,433 --> 00:17:53,567
My Aunt Alicia and her family
are staying with me.

329
00:17:53,700 --> 00:17:55,400
And my niece, too.

330
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:57,633
I'm sorry.

331
00:17:57,767 --> 00:17:59,167
Hey, Wiro.

332
00:17:59,300 --> 00:18:03,533
Why do you seem to be pushing
Emma towards that Logan?

333
00:18:03,667 --> 00:18:05,000
What are you?

334
00:18:05,133 --> 00:18:06,733
A pimp?

335
00:18:06,867 --> 00:18:08,200
Silly. Of course not.

336
00:18:08,333 --> 00:18:09,533
And why not?

337
00:18:09,667 --> 00:18:11,167
Danilo has Jade.

338
00:18:11,300 --> 00:18:13,067
Can't Emma have Logan?

339
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:13,900
That's right.

340
00:18:14,033 --> 00:18:15,433
Wiro has a point.

341
00:18:15,567 --> 00:18:20,800
Emma can also hire me
at Logan's bar.

342
00:18:20,933 --> 00:18:22,900
Ouch!

343
00:18:23,067 --> 00:18:24,500
We better go.

344
00:18:24,633 --> 00:18:25,533
Let's leave them for now.

345
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:27,067
I'm listening.

346
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,100
Ouch.

347
00:18:28,233 --> 00:18:29,300
You're pushing her.

348
00:18:29,433 --> 00:18:30,167
Where?

349
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:31,500
Go inside. Go!

350
00:18:31,633 --> 00:18:34,667
You know what?
I like your friends.

351
00:18:34,800 --> 00:18:38,133
Can we sit down?

352
00:18:38,267 --> 00:18:39,367
Okay.

353
00:18:52,967 --> 00:18:56,300
Okay, I'll go back there.

354
00:18:56,467 --> 00:18:59,500
I have nowhere
else to go anyway.

355
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:03,300
But promise me

356
00:19:03,433 --> 00:19:06,467
that we're not going to talk
about your feelings.

357
00:19:08,633 --> 00:19:10,467
Because I have no time for that.

358
00:19:12,133 --> 00:19:15,500
Mookie is my priority for now.

359
00:19:15,633 --> 00:19:19,400
I need to figure out how
I can get her back from Jade.

360
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,333
- What did she say?
- There's so many ants!

361
00:19:20,467 --> 00:19:21,600
Yeah.

362
00:19:25,767 --> 00:19:27,833
Okay.

363
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,867
I'm good with it.

364
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,600
And I won't insist on
my feelings anymore.

365
00:19:31,733 --> 00:19:33,000
Promise.

366
00:19:33,133 --> 00:19:34,600
So don't get mad at me, okay?

367
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:40,033
I can't get mad at you.

368
00:19:40,167 --> 00:19:41,967
You helped me a lot.

369
00:19:43,933 --> 00:19:47,233
But I don't want
to see you for now.

370
00:19:47,367 --> 00:19:50,067
And talk about your feelings.

371
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:53,567
And please stay out of my plans.

372
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:55,267
Let me get Mookie back...

373
00:19:57,267 --> 00:19:59,100
on my own.

374
00:19:59,233 --> 00:20:01,867
Okay.

375
00:20:02,033 --> 00:20:03,467
Don't worry.

376
00:20:03,600 --> 00:20:06,100
I'll be hands-off with that.

377
00:20:06,233 --> 00:20:07,333
I'll let you do your thing,
Emma.

378
00:20:08,767 --> 00:20:15,133
From now on, I'm only here
to remind you to be careful.

379
00:20:19,367 --> 00:20:23,167
Guys, see you later at 7:00 PM
at Buboy's Gastro Pub.

380
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:25,133
Don't miss it.

381
00:20:25,267 --> 00:20:25,700
Yes.

382
00:20:25,833 --> 00:20:27,133
I'll wait for you.

383
00:20:27,267 --> 00:20:28,333
Yes.

384
00:20:31,067 --> 00:20:32,033
Dad!

385
00:20:32,167 --> 00:20:34,167
Dear. Mookie.

386
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,167
How are you?

387
00:20:35,333 --> 00:20:37,600
You find Mookie so beautiful,
don't you?

388
00:20:37,733 --> 00:20:38,833
Of course.

389
00:20:38,967 --> 00:20:41,000
That's the face I like.

390
00:20:41,133 --> 00:20:43,967
Simple, but wow.

391
00:20:44,100 --> 00:20:46,133
Goodness!

392
00:20:46,267 --> 00:20:47,667
Let's go.

393
00:20:47,800 --> 00:20:49,933
You might pursue her
if we stay any longer.

394
00:20:50,067 --> 00:20:52,867
I'll be envious.

395
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,267
Bye, Mooks!

396
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,633
Bye!

397
00:20:55,767 --> 00:20:57,000
Let's go, Dad.

398
00:21:08,500 --> 00:21:10,333
Everybody, listen.

399
00:21:10,467 --> 00:21:14,633
When they come, we will say
"Congratulations!"

400
00:21:14,767 --> 00:21:15,700
Is that good?

401
00:21:15,833 --> 00:21:18,800
- Clear?
- Clear!

402
00:21:18,933 --> 00:21:21,067
Mooks, where are your parents?

403
00:21:21,200 --> 00:21:22,233
They're on their way here.

404
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,567
Guys, I will cue you.

405
00:21:33,233 --> 00:21:34,567
They're here.

406
00:21:42,800 --> 00:21:45,267
Love, are you sure we're
going to have dinner here?

407
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:46,400
- Yes.
- This place gives

408
00:21:46,533 --> 00:21:47,967
a different vibe.

409
00:21:48,100 --> 00:21:48,567
I know.

410
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:52,600
Congratulations!

411
00:21:52,733 --> 00:21:53,967
What's this?

412
00:21:54,100 --> 00:21:55,000
- Mookie.
- Oh my gosh!

413
00:21:55,133 --> 00:21:56,833
Thank you!

414
00:21:56,967 --> 00:21:58,100
Mookie!

415
00:21:58,233 --> 00:22:01,467
I thought it was only the three
of us who would have dinner.

416
00:22:01,600 --> 00:22:02,867
Thank you, guys!

417
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:05,300
- Love, they surprised us!
- I know.

418
00:22:05,433 --> 00:22:06,300
Thank you.

419
00:22:06,433 --> 00:22:10,333
Thank you all for being here!

420
00:22:10,467 --> 00:22:17,267
I planned this for you
and Dad, Mommy Jade.

421
00:22:17,433 --> 00:22:19,767
Thank you, baby girl.

422
00:22:19,900 --> 00:22:21,933
I love it.

423
00:22:22,067 --> 00:22:24,000
Thank you.

424
00:22:24,133 --> 00:22:24,967
Go on.

425
00:22:25,100 --> 00:22:27,133
Enjoy yourselves.

426
00:22:27,267 --> 00:22:29,667
Let's have fun, everyone!

427
00:22:39,800 --> 00:22:41,067
Oh, Dear.

428
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:46,267
Maybe we need a drink.

429
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,667
Wait, I'll get us
something to drink.

430
00:22:47,800 --> 00:22:49,433
Yes, get my usual favorite.

431
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:50,500
Please order it for me.

432
00:22:50,633 --> 00:22:52,033
Okay. I will.

433
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:58,133
I'll go over here.

434
00:22:58,267 --> 00:22:59,567
Noel.

435
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:02,167
- Bro.
- Thank you for coming.

436
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:08,833
I knew it. It was you.

437
00:23:08,967 --> 00:23:10,433
What are you doing here?

438
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:12,733
You, creepy stalker.

439
00:23:23,833 --> 00:23:26,133
That smells familiar.

440
00:23:26,267 --> 00:23:30,067
The scent of jealousy.

441
00:23:30,800 --> 00:23:33,567
I'm not jealous
of you and Danilo.

442
00:23:33,700 --> 00:23:34,833
Oh, really?

443
00:23:36,333 --> 00:23:41,600
But why do you seem
you're about to cry?

444
00:23:41,733 --> 00:23:43,767
You can have him
all you want.

445
00:23:43,900 --> 00:23:47,000
You drove me crazy
to get my family.

446
00:23:47,133 --> 00:23:48,767
Congratulations.

447
00:23:48,900 --> 00:23:51,200
Because you were successful.

448
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:53,733
So keep Danilo to yourself.

449
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:56,933
All I need is Mookie.

450
00:23:58,267 --> 00:24:00,733
But, Emma, what do we do?

451
00:24:00,867 --> 00:24:04,767
Mookie doesn't want
you anymore too.

452
00:24:04,900 --> 00:24:07,600
I won't stop trying
to win her over.

453
00:24:07,733 --> 00:24:09,967
Until she gets tired
of pushing me away.

454
00:24:10,100 --> 00:24:13,033
Until she listens to me
and believes what I say.

455
00:24:13,167 --> 00:24:14,767
I won't stop.

456
00:24:23,267 --> 00:24:26,800
I think I already
know Emma's weakness.

457
00:24:26,933 --> 00:24:31,300
It's seeing Danilo, Mookie,
and I together.

458
00:24:31,467 --> 00:24:35,833
She gets distracted whenever she
sees us together.

459
00:24:35,967 --> 00:24:39,467
If Jade wants to play dirty,
then mess with her too.

460
00:24:39,600 --> 00:24:40,033
How?

461
00:24:40,167 --> 00:24:41,200
Use me.

462
00:24:41,333 --> 00:24:44,633
Logan, is this our table?

463
00:24:44,767 --> 00:24:45,300
Emma?

464
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:46,500
- Emma?
- Logan?

465
00:24:49,633 --> 00:24:51,667
The two are in an
awkward silence.

466
00:24:52,600 --> 00:24:53,100
Really?

467
00:24:53,233 --> 00:24:55,100
Her eyes show annoyance.

468
00:24:55,233 --> 00:24:57,267
You're enjoying it so much.

469
00:24:57,400 --> 00:25:00,067
Don't tell me you still
have feelings for your ex?

470
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:01,933
I do.

471
00:25:02,100 --> 00:25:05,433
Anger, wrath, deep disgust,
and hatred.
